      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic isotropic material model for titanium alloy screw and UHMWPE test block justified by strain range observed in F1717 test. Contact formulation validated against analytical contact solutions.",
      "rationale": "Peak strains in the screw shank remain below 0.5% in the elastic regime for loads up to yield, justifying linear elasticity. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation compared against Hertzian contact benchmarks with < 2% error. Geometric nonlinearity (large displacement) included to capture post-yield bending response. Gradation 3 justified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
