      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative hardware. Dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design nominal. Two independent laboratories contribute samples.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled using production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and ASTM F1717 UHMWPE test blocks. CMM inspection confirmed all critical dimensions within drawing tolerances. Constructs assembled at two independent laboratories (FDA/CDRH and DePuy Synthes) to assess inter-laboratory variability. Gradation 3 met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 protocol including load rate, fixture geometry, and environmental conditions. Multiple load rates or conditions assessed to characterize sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "All testing performed per ASTM F1717 at a single crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min at ambient temperature. Only one test condition evaluated; sensitivity to load rate and temperature not characterized. This factor falls below the required Gradation 3, representing a known gap accepted by the team given the standardized nature of the F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
